      {
         "id": "SECTION_introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Growth</h3>In a previous text, we explored how indigenous peoples did not expand their numerical values from right to left. Instead, they chose to grow their numbers in the direction we associate with growth—the vertical (<htcite0>). In this text, we will learn how indigenous cultures represented even larger numbers.</p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "b1a262fc-0148-489b-8b70-5266a85c1e67",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Numerical Families (Part II)",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "07",
                        "day": "01"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2024",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_mesoamerica",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Mesoamerican numbers</h3>We can represent any decimal number within the Mesoamerican numerical system. However, it is important to note that this representation is an approximation, as it does not precisely align with the Mesoamerican calendar (<htcite0> ; <htcite1> ; <htcite2> ; <htcite3>). Additionally, we must remember that we only advance to the next numerical \"generation\" after reaching the number 19, rather than 9, as in the decimal system. With this in mind, we can rewrite Table 3 from the previous page (<htcite4>):</p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "ad11b3b2-8cdf-4d71-9cb7-2ac241850945",
                     "text": "Casares Contreras, Orlando & Cetina, José & Cabrera, Venus Sarahí",
                     "page": "pp. 26 - 29, 34 (ResearchGate)",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2022",
                        "month": "07",
                        "day": "25"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "eca99877-c520-4569-a71c-0a5b3dd77dc4",
                     "text": "Casares Contreras, Orlando & Cetina, José & Cabrera, Venus Sarahí",
                     "page": "pp. 26 - 29, 34 (Revista)",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2022",
                        "month": "07",
