            {
               "text": "<p><table id=\"yupana0\" class=\"tawapukllay\"> <tr><th>King (<i>Ajaw</i>)</th><th>Generation</th><th>Order</th><th>Decimal Orders</th><th>First Number</th><th>Last Number</th></tr> <tr><td><i>Yax Pasaj Chan Yopaat</i></td><td>Son</td><td><i>K'iin</i></td><td>Ones and Tens</td><td><b>0</b></td><td><b>19</b></td></tr> <tr><td><i>K’ahk’ Yipyaj Chan K’awiil</i></td><td>Father</td><td><i>Winal</i></td><td>Tens and Hundreds</td><td><b>20</b></td><td><b>399</b></td></tr> <tr><td><i>Waxaklajuun Ubaah K’awiil</i></td><td>Grandfather</td><td><i>Tun</i></td><td>Hundreds and Thousands</td><td><b>400</b></td><td><b>7.999</b></td></tr> <tr><td><i>K’ahk Uti’ Witz’ K’awiil</i></td><td>1st Great-Grandfather</td><td><i>K'atun</i></td><td>Thousands, Ten Thousands and Hundred Thousands</td><td><b>8.000</b></td><td><b>159.999</b></td></tr> <tr><td><i>Butz’ Chan</i></td><td>2nd Great-Grandfather</td><td><i>Bak'tun</i></td><td>Hundred Thousands and Millions</td><td><b>160.000</b></td><td><b>3.199.999</b></td></tr> <tr><td><i>Tzi B’alam</i></td><td>3rd Great-Grandfather</td><td><i>Piktun</i></td><td>Millions and Tens Millions</td><td><b>3.200.000</b></td><td><b>63.999.999</b></td></tr> <tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td>4th Great-Grandfather</td><td><i>Kalabtun</i></td><td>Tens and Hundreds Millions. Billions</td><td><b>64.000.000</b></td><td><b>1.279.999.999</b></td></tr> <tr><td><i>Wi’ Yohl K’inich</i></td><td>5th Great-Grandfather</td><td><i>Kinchiltun</i></td><td>Billions and Tens Billions</td><td><b>1.280.000.000</b></td><td><b>25.599.999.999</b></td></tr> <tr><td><i>Bahlam Nehn</i></td><td>6th Great-Grandfather</td><td><i>Alautun</i></td><td>Tens Billions and Hundred Billions</td><td><b>25.600.000.000</b></td><td><b>511.999.999.999</b></td></tr> <tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td>7th Great-Grandfather</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>Tens Billions and Hundred Billions</td><td><b>512.000.000.000</b></td><td><b>10.239.999.999.999</b></td></tr> </table></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p class=\"desc\"><b>Table 1</b>: Numerical limits and the family.<br />The names of the kings (<i>Ajawob</i>) mentioned in this table are documented by Anastasia Hutnick, Catherine Docter, and Dorie R. Budet (<htcite0> ; <htcite1>).<br />The generational names were sourced from the \"Dicionário de Genealogia\" by Gilber Rubim Rangel (<htcite2> ;<htcite3> ; <htcite4>).</p><p>We would like to highlight three features of this table: First, the name of the final numerical order remains unknown (<htcite5>). Second, the numerical system's 20 symbols (numbers) enable representation of larger quantities within each positional value. Third, while we treat the kings didactically as consecutive generations, those depicted on the altar do not actually represent consecutive generations. We will explore these mathematical concepts further for better understanding (<htcite6>).</p><p>To see how decimal numbers are represented in the vigesimal numerical system, you can enter a number in the text field and then click the <i class=\"fa-solid fa-play\" style=\"color: Tomato;\" name=\"ignoreme\"></i> button:</p>",
